    <div class="container">
        <section id="about">
            <p>Many schools enforce rigid dress codes and appearance rules that limit gender expression, disproportionately affecting students who don't conform to traditional norms. These restrictions often lead to exclusion, stigma, and mental health challenges such as anxiety and low self-esteem. To foster a safe and inclusive environment, it's essential for schools to adopt policies that support the diverse ways students express their gender, ensuring freedom from discrimination and promoting well-being for all.</p>
        </section>
        <section id="objectives">
            <h2>Objectives</h2>
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-item">
                    <img src="https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/D5612AQEAPdO0Suhr1Q/article-cover_image-shrink_720_1280/0/1709795392663?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=kPVY0r0thT_QTpQ0AKR9zLPBeGmvVcrcQZTiWLSXzk8" alt="Inclusivity">
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <h3>Promote Inclusivity</h3>
                        <p>Organizations and educational institutions should actively update policies to recognize and support diverse gender identities. This includes adapting dress codes, providing gender-neutral restrooms, and respecting chosen names and pronouns, creating a more welcoming and equitable environment.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card-item">
                    <img src="https://cureclcn4.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/raise_awareness.jpg" alt="Awareness">
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <h3>Raise Awareness</h3>
                        <p>Conduct targeted workshops, seminars, and media campaigns to educate communities about gender diversity. These initiatives aim to build understanding and acceptance, breaking down prejudices and creating a culture of empathy and respect.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card-item">
                    <img src="https://media.ktoo.org/2015/08/rainbow-flag.jpg" alt="Safe spaces">
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <h3>Create Safe Spaces</h3>
                        <p>Establish secure, judgment-free areas where individuals can express themselves openly without fear of discrimination or harassment. These spaces serve as vital resources for emotional and social support, helping students thrive.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        <section id="significance">
            <h2>Significance</h2>
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-item">
                    <img src="https://www.eo-executiveoptical.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/planthead.webp" alt="Mental Health">
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <h3>Improved Mental Health</h3>
                        <p>Inclusive practices directly contribute to better mental health outcomes by fostering environments where students feel seen, valued, and supported. This can reduce feelings of isolation and increase overall well-being.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card-item">
                    <img src="https://web.uri.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/1063/success-module-motivation.png" alt="Academic Success">
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <h3>Increased Academic Success</h3>
                        <p>When students feel safe and included, their focus and engagement in academic activities improve. Supportive educational settings can help unlock studentsâ€™ full potential and lead to higher achievement levels.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card-item">
                    <img src="https://ieg.worldbankgroup.org/sites/default/files/Data/styles/reader_publication_cover_desktop/public/2021-03/webpage_GenderMTR.jpg?itok=GNhhsfga" alt="Bullying Reduction">
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <h3>Reduction in Bullying</h3>
                        <p>Implementing inclusivity measures and fostering awareness helps diminish bullying by addressing ignorance and fostering a culture of mutual respect. This leads to a safer and more positive environment for all.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        <section id="scope">
            <h2>Scope</h2>
            <p>The project will be piloted in a secondary school with a comprehensive approach involving students, staff, and parents to foster greater acceptance and inclusivity. Key components include revising dress code policies to be gender-neutral, allowing students to express their gender identity freely, and conducting educational campaigns to raise awareness about gender diversity. The initiative also establishes peer support groups and safe spaces, while providing mental health services tailored to gender identity issues. The project's impact will be evaluated through surveys, with the goal of expanding it district-wide to promote inclusivity in other schools.</p>
        </section>
